<plot>Every year, from the cliff-tops of Beachy Head, an average of 38 people throw themselves to their deaths. Now Eastbourne window-cleaner spends his days patrolling the 8 mile stretch of coastline, keeping a tireless watch over the notorious suicide spot. To date, Keith has prevented 25 from taking their own lives. What drives a man to such dedication?</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?600030</url></doc>
